facultyInfo:
Our Ceramics studio offers a selection of glazes and tools, as well as a kick wheel, fifteen wheels, a slab roller, and electric kilns. Kilns are operated by the studio technician only, and cone 6 clay must be used for all work. For your convenience, clay can be purchased from the technician for $35 per bag or $5 per lump. Technicians are available during drop-in times.
 All members using our Ceramics Studio are required to complete a two-hour safety workshop with the technician (contact the studio technician to book an appointment).
 Happy crafting!

facultyInfo:
Our woodworking studio is a great place to set up your next independent project. The studio technician is available during drop-in times and must approve all project proposals (for materials, equipment, and storage), and agree to any delivery of materials. Heavy machinery is only available during drop-in times (including tablesaw, bandsaw, drill press, lathe, mini lathe, hollow chisel mortiser, spindle sander, edge sander, mitre saw, scroll saw, router table and down draft table).
 Members using the studio are required to complete a two-hour safety workshop with the technician (at an additional fee), and successfully complete a safety test. Please contact the studio technician to book an appointment.
 Happy building!

Our Digital Arts studio is equipped with thirteen computer stations, featuring Apple iMac 27 Intel i5 3.1Ghz, 16GB DDR3 RAM, AMD HD 6970m video card. Members are expected to be able to work independently, and exhibit a good understanding of the MacIntosh computer equipment and software. Technicians are available in the building, and a digital scanner stations and a HP Colour LaserJet CP3525n (printing fees may apply) are located in the studio. Software includes Adobes Creative Suite 5.5, Adobe Photoshop Lightroom 5, Apple Final Cut Pro x, Apple Logic 9, and Microsoft Office 2010.
 If you need some help, one and two hour intro classes to working with Mac Computers are available. Please see the studio technician about registration info.
 Happy designing!

Our Fine Arts studio is the perfect place to do all your drawing, painting, and sculpting activities. Paint options include watercolour, acrylic, and water based oils only. At the studio, youll have access to tables, chairs, stools, easels, drawing donkeys, drying racks, slop sinks, and WiFi. Materials such as papers and paints are available at the front desk for an extra fee.
 Individuals are expected to exhibit a good understanding of the materials, tools and processes to safely work independently. Members are responsible for cleaning up after themselves.
 Happy painting!

Our Textile studio is perfect for all your fibre-related activities. Whether you sew, quilt, knit, or weave, this studio is a great, clean and open space that gives you plenty of room to complete your projects. Individuals are expected to have good understanding of the materials and processes so they can work safely on their own.
 Locker space is available at the front desk at an extra cost. This is a dry studio, and wet materials are not permitted. Access is limited to September through June only.
 Happy sewing!
